    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-06-28T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-06-28T06:00:00-05:00" n="131"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d131">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/6–2850: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-06-28T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 28, 1950—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 28—8:56 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">JUNE 28, 1950</p>
                <p rend="center">(Wednesday)</p>
                <p>1754. Embassy welcomes public announcement re Korea by President noting
                    modifications original statement contained Deptel 541,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d131fn1">Telegram 3124, June 27, 1 a. m., to London, <ref
                            target="#pg_186">p. 186</ref>, was repeated to Moscow as telegram
                        541.</note> June 27. In our view this firm stand exactly what is necessary
                    to serve notice to Soviets that Communists have gone too far. Needless to say US
                    action will prove tremendous influence all areas threatened by Communist
                    aggression, and effects in Asia should become manifest shortly.</p>
                <p>Repeated information London 264, Paris 251, <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>
                    44, Tokyo 26, Department pass London, Paris, <gloss target="#t_USUN1"
                        >USUN</gloss>, Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
